race.comment: Looks a cracking BM64 with plenty of progressive types. JOB DONE (4) looks the one to beat, especially given the main danger has scratched. He resumes having won very well on debut at Seymour which saw him start $3.50 in the 2yo Final at Flemington over the Winter. He maps nicely just behind the speed and should take beating. SATIN DIVA (11) resumes with a nice profile. She's started $1.30 and $1.14 in two starts to date, winning her maiden nicely at Moe before the break. There's clearly ability there and she can deliver. ESPANA (7) is a bit more exposed but won well last time and maps for a soft run. She'll track the speed and be hard to hold out. CAVALRY GIRL (2) wasn't beaten far in a decent 3yo race at Flemington last time and will give a sight up on speed.
